chip-desktop-configs (0.3) trixie; urgency=low

  * openbox autostart: start + empty-unlock gnome-keyring before nm-applet. nm-applet
    persists Wi-Fi PSKs through the Secret Service (libsecret); with no running keyring
    the password was never stored and NetworkManager failed on the next boot with
    "secrets were required, but not provided" (gui-only -- headless/pocketchip use
    nmtui, which stores PSKs system-owned). Pairs with gnome-keyring added to the gui
    package list.

 -- Ben Young <computermouth@proton.me>  Wed, 24 Jun 2026 12:00:00 -0500

